<subSubSection pageId="56" pageNumber="57" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="56.[151,1436,1701,2008]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1741,1767]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schellenberg, A." box="[333,578,1742,1768]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" refId="ref29946" refString="Schellenberg, A. (1925) Crustacea VIII: Amphipoda. pp. 111 - 204 in W. Michaelsen (ed.) Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Meeresfauna Westafrikas. L. Friedrichsen &amp; Co., Hamburg." type="book" year="1925">Schellenberg (1925)</bibRefCitation>
did not illustrate 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[810,1039,1742,1767]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Verdeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subchelata">
<emphasis box="[810,1039,1742,1767]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Verdeia subchelata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. K.H. 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnard, K. H." box="[1132,1321,1742,1768]" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 326" refId="ref27326" refString="Barnard, K. H. (1932) Amphipoda. Discovery Reports, 5, 1 - 326, pl. 1." type="journal article" year="1932">Barnard (1932)</bibRefCitation>
, the first reviewer, illustrated an enlarged male gnathopod 2 and showed that this was a distinct species, but the figures here are the first complete illustrations of the species. Based on gnathopod 2, this species appears to be most closely related to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chevreux" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[361,541,1862,1887]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Verdeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandimana">
<emphasis box="[361,541,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">D. grandimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[658,794,1862,1888]" name="Cape Verde" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">Cape Verde</collectingCountry>
Islands. The main differences are that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Chevreux" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[1256,1436,1862,1887]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Verdeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandimana">
<emphasis box="[1256,1436,1862,1887]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">D. grandimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 3 spines on the palm of male gnathopod 2 and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[744,907,1902,1927]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Verdeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="56" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subchelata">
<emphasis box="[744,907,1902,1927]" italics="true" pageId="56" pageNumber="57">D. subchelata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 2 spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
